---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="rider-waite recoloured">
  <article class="project-page">

    <header class="project-header">
      <h1>rider-waite recoloured</h1>
      <div class="project-meta mono muted">
        <span>2026</span>
        <span>scraping / image processing / automation</span>
        <a href="https://github.com/cabi-net/rider-waite-scrape-and-index" target="_blank" rel="noopener">github ↗</a>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section class="project-body">

      <p>
        A Python script that scrapes all 78 Rider-Waite Tarot card images from
        Wikimedia Commons and recolours every card using a custom 4-anchor LAB ramp palette — inspired by
        Krita's Index Colors filter, reimplemented from scratch in Python and applied
        entirely at runtime.
      </p>

      <p>
        The palette is built from four ordered anchors — Shadow, Base, Light, Bright —
        whose colours and number of intermediate steps the user defines. The script
        linearly interpolates between each adjacent pair in CIE LAB space, then snaps
        every pixel to its nearest palette entry by Euclidean LAB distance. Output directories and palette swatches are
        auto-named from the settings, so every run is reproducible and self-documenting.
      </p>

      <div class="example">

<div class="code-block">
          <p class="mono muted label">terminal</p>
          <pre class="mono"><span class="prompt">$</span> python rider_waite_krita_index.py \
--shadow 3f32ac --base 76428a --light 5fcde4 --bright ffffff \
--steps 4 4 4</pre>
        </div>

        <div class="swatch-row">
          <div class="swatch-col">
            <p class="mono muted label">anchor colours</p>
            <img src="/assets/rider-waite/anchor_swatches.png" alt="anchor swatches" class="palette" />
          </div>
          <div class="swatch-col">
            <p class="mono muted label">generated palette</p>
            <img src="/assets/rider-waite/palette.png" alt="palette ramp" class="palette" />
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="mono muted label">recoloured cards</p>
        <div class="card-grid">
          <figure>
            <img src="/assets/rider-waite/ace_of_cups-in.png" alt="Ace of Cups — original" />
            <figcaption class="mono muted">original</figcaption>
          </figure>
          <figure>
            <img src="/assets/rider-waite/ace_of_cups-out.png" alt="Ace of Cups — recoloured" />
            <figcaption class="mono muted">recoloured</figcaption>
          </figure>
          <figure>
            <img src="/assets/rider-waite/the_empress-in.png" alt="The Empress — original" />
            <figcaption class="mono muted">original</figcaption>
          </figure>
          <figure>
            <img src="/assets/rider-waite/the_empress-out.png" alt="The Empress — recoloured" />
            <figcaption class="mono muted">recoloured</figcaption>
          </figure>
          <figure>
            <img src="/assets/rider-waite/the_sun-in.png" alt="The Sun — original" />
            <figcaption class="mono muted">original</figcaption>
          </figure>
          <figure>
            <img src="/assets/rider-waite/the_sun-out.png" alt="The Sun — recoloured" />
            <figcaption class="mono muted">recoloured</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>

      </div>


      <p class="muted mono status">
        The generated cards are used in an oracle tarot reader — interactive embed forthcoming.
      </p>

    </section>

  </article>
</Base>

<style>
.project-page { max-width: 720px; }

.project-header { margin-bottom: var(--space-xl); }

h1 {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-size: var(--size-3xl);
  font-weight: normal;
  margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
}

.project-meta {
  display: flex;
  gap: var(--space-lg);
  font-size: var(--size-xs);
}

.project-body p {
  max-width: 65ch;
  line-height: 1.8;
}

.project-body p + p { margin-top: var(--space-lg); }

.example {
  margin: var(--space-xl) 0;
}

.section-label {
  font-size: var(--size-xs);
  margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
}

.swatch-row {
  display: flex;
  gap: var(--space-xl);
  margin: var(--space-lg) 0;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
}

.swatch-col .label {
  font-size: var(--size-xs);
  margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
}

.palette {
  max-width: 280px;
  image-rendering: pixelated;
}

.card-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  gap: var(--space-lg) var(--space-xl);
  margin: var(--space-xl) 0;
  max-width: 560px;
}

.card-grid figure img {
  width: 100%;
}

.card-grid figcaption {
  margin-top: var(--space-xs);
  font-size: var(--size-xs);
}

.code-block {
  margin: var(--space-xl) 0;
  padding: var(--space-lg);
  background: var(--bg-surface);
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
}

.prompt {
  color: var(--fg-muted);
  user-select: none;
}

.code-block .label {
  font-size: var(--size-xs);
  margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
}

.code-block pre {
  font-size: var(--size-sm);
  line-height: 1.8;
  white-space: pre-wrap;
}

.divider {
  border: none;
  border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  margin: var(--space-2xl) 0;
}

.status {
  margin-top: var(--space-xl);
  font-size: var(--size-xs);
}
</style>